'''Ali Taramakhi''' or '''Elî Teremaxî''', was a [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] linguist and writer in the 16th century. He is credited for writing the first [[Arabic grammar]] book in the [[Kurdish language]] in 1591. His book is titled, ''Serfa Kurmancî'' or ''Tesrîf''. He wrote the book in order to allow Kurdish pupils to learn and study Arabic more easily. This work was later expanded by Male Younis Halkataini (died 1785). The book has 33 chapters covering different aspects of the Arabic [[grammar]].
==Books== #''Serfa Kurmancî'', Pencinar Publishers, Sverige/Stockholm, 140 p., {{ISBN|91-972779-4-0}}, 1997.
==References== #[https://web.archive.org/web/20060927153126/http://www.kurdishacademy.org/english/articles/articles-012.html The Kurdish Language: from Oral Tradition to Written Language], By Dr. Jemal [[Nebez]]. (see ''Taramakhi'') #Ali Taramakhi, [https://web.archive.org/web/20060303105705/http://hem.bredband.net/serkay/Doc/Pirtuk/pirtuk-b/Nr-15.htm Serfa Kurmancî].
