'''Muhnot Nainsi''' (1610–1670) is known for his studies of the region now encompassed by the state of [[Rajasthan]] in India.

His works include ''Marwar Ra Pargana Ri Vigat'' and ''Nainsi Ri Khyat''. He was [[Dewan]] of [[Marwar]] during the reign of [[Jaswant Singh of Marwar|Jaswant Singh]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Studies In Indian History: Rajasthan Through The Ages The Heritage Of Rajputs (Set Of 5 Vols.) |first1=R. K. |last1=Gupta |first2=S. R. |last2=Bakshi |publisher=Sarup & Sons |year=2008 |page=100 |isbn=978-81-7625-841-8 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gPPZHK2ZfLoC&pg=PA100 |accessdate=2011-09-28}}</ref>

munsi deviprasad compares nainsi to abul-fasal.

